quran[62]{c,v,t}:
  53,1,By the star when it sets
  53,2,"Your companion [the Prophet] has neither strayed nor is he deluded"
  53,3,Nor does he speak out of his own desire
  53,4,"It is but a revelation sent down [to him]"
  53,5,"He was taught by [an angel of] mighty power"
  53,6,"and of great perfection, who manifested himself [in his true form]"
  53,7,when he was on the higher horizon
  53,8,"Then he approached [the Prophet] and descended"
  53,9,until he was only two bow-lengths away or even closer
  53,10,Then he revealed to His slave what he had to reveal
  53,11,"The [Prophet’s] heart did not deny what he saw"
  53,12,Do you dispute with him concerning what he saw
  53,13,He certainly saw him a second time
  53,14,"at the Lote Tree of the Utmost Boundary [in the seventh heaven]"
  53,15,near which is the Garden of Abode
  53,16,"when the Lote Tree was overwhelmed with [divine] splendors"
  53,17,"His gaze did not wander, nor did it look beyond the limit"
  53,18,He certainly saw some of the greatest signs of his Lord
  53,19,"Have you [O disbelievers] thought about [the idols of] al-Lāt and al-‘Uzzā"
  53,20,"and Manāt, the third one as well"
  53,21,Do you choose for yourselves males and for Him females
  53,22,That is then an unfair division
  53,23,"These [idols] are no more than names you and your forefathers have made up, for which Allah has not sent down any authority. They follow nothing but conjecture and what their souls desire, although there has come to them guidance from their Lord"
  53,24,Is it that man can get whatever he wishes for
  53,25,"Rather, to Allah belongs the Hereafter and this world"
  53,26,How many angels there are in the heavens whose intercession will be of no avail except after Allah’s permission to whom He wills and pleases
  53,27,"Indeed, those who do not believe in the Hereafter give the angels female names"
  53,28,"They have no knowledge about it. They only follow conjecture, but conjecture is of no avail against the truth"
  53,29,So pay no heed to those who turn away from Our message and who only seek the life of this world
  53,30,"That is the limit of their knowledge. Indeed, your Lord knows best who has strayed from His Way, and He knows best who is guided"
  53,31,"To Allah belongs all that is in the heavens and all that is on earth, so that He may recompense the evildoers for what they did, and reward those who do good with the best reward"
  53,32,"those who avoid major sins and shameful acts, except for minor lapses. Indeed, your Lord is ample in forgiveness. He knows you best, as He created you from the earth and when you were fetuses in the wombs of your mothers. So do not claim purity for yourselves, for He knows best who is truly righteous"
  53,33,"Have you seen the one who turned away [from Islam]"
  53,34,"who gave a little, and then stopped"
  53,35,"Does he have knowledge of the unseen, so he has insight"
  53,36,Or has he not been informed of what is in the Scriptures of Moses
  53,37,"and of Abraham, who fulfilled his duty"
  53,38,That no bearer of burden will bear the burden of another
  53,39,and that man will not receive except what he strives for
  53,40,and that his efforts will be examined
  53,41,then he will be recompensed in full
  53,42,and that to your Lord is the final return
  53,43,and that He is the One Who makes people laugh and weep
  53,44,and that He is the One Who causes death and gives life
  53,45,"and that He created the pairs, male and female"
  53,46,from an emitted drop of sperm
  53,47,and it is upon Him to bring about the second creation
  53,48,And He is the One Who enriches and bestows wealth
  53,49,"and that He is the Lord of Sirius [a star worshiped before Islam]"
  53,50,"And that He destroyed the earlier ‘Ād [people of Hūd]"
  53,51,"and Thamūd [people of Sālih], sparing none"
  53,52,"and [He destroyed] the people of Noah before them; they were indeed more wicked and more rebellious"
  53,53,"And He toppled the cities [of Sodom and Gomorrah] upside down"
  53,54,"and they were utterly covered [by stones]"
  53,55,Then which of the favors of your Lord do you doubt
  53,56,"This [Prophet] is a warner like the earlier warners"
  53,57,The imminent Hour has drawn near
  53,58,none but Allah can disclose it
  53,59,Do you find this discourse astonishing
  53,60,"and you laugh [at it] and not weep"
  53,61,while persisting in heedlessness
  53,62,"So prostrate to Allah and worship [Him]"